SIMPLE: freighter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freighter
<hw>Freight"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
loads a ship, or one who charters and loads a ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One employed in receiving and forwarding
freight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One for whom freight is transported.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A vessel used mainly to carry freight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freightless</ent>⟦br⟧
